# Ethic Companion Design System Rules

This document provides comprehensive guidance for integrating Figma designs using the Model Context Protocol (MCP) into the Ethic Companion frontend.

---

## 1. Token Definitions

### Location
Design tokens are defined in `/app/globals.css` using CSS custom properties.

### Format
Tokens use **HSL color format** (without the `hsl()` wrapper) for flexibility:

```css
/* /app/globals.css */
:root {
  --background: 0 0% 100%;        /* H S% L% format */
  --foreground: 240 10% 3.9%;
  --primary: 240 5.9% 10%;
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  /* ... */
}
```

### Color Token Mapping

| Token Name | Light Mode | Dark Mode | Usage |
|------------|------------|-----------|-------|
| `--background` | White | Near-black | Page backgrounds |
| `--foreground` | Dark slate | White | Primary text |
| `--primary` | Dark slate | White | Buttons, links |
| `--primary-foreground` | White | Dark | Text on primary |
| `--secondary` | Light gray | Dark gray | Secondary buttons |
| `--muted` | Light gray | Dark gray | Muted backgrounds |
| `--muted-foreground` | Medium gray | Light gray | Secondary text |
| `--accent` | Light gray | Dark gray | Hover states |
| `--destructive` | Red | Dark red | Error states |
| `--border` | Light gray | Dark gray | Borders |
| `--card` | White | Near-black | Card backgrounds |

### Sidebar-Specific Tokens
```css
--sidebar: 0 0% 98%;
--sidebar-foreground: 240 5.3% 26.1%;
--sidebar-primary: 240 5.9% 10%;
--sidebar-accent: 240 4.8% 95.9%;
--sidebar-border: 220 13% 91%;
```

### Radius Tokens
```css
--radius: 0.5rem;              /* Base: 8px */
--radius-sm: calc(var(--radius) - 4px);   /* 4px */
--radius-md: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);   /* 6px */
--radius-lg: var(--radius);               /* 8px */
--radius-xl: calc(var(--radius) + 4px);   /* 12px */
```

### Theme Integration
Tokens are exposed to Tailwind via `@theme inline` block:
```css
@theme inline {
  --color-background: hsl(var(--background));
  --color-primary: hsl(var(--primary));
  /* ... */
}
```

### Figma to Token Mapping

| Figma Color | Project Token |
|-------------|---------------|
| `#4f46e5` (Indigo) | Use `primary` or gradient |
| `#1e293b` (Slate 800) | `foreground` |
| `#475569` (Slate 600) | `muted-foreground` |
| `#f8fafc` (Slate 50) | `secondary` / `muted` |
| `#e2e8f0` (Slate 200) | `border` |

